      "content": "Allowing religious groups to opt-out of certain government mandates, especially those related to healthcare or civil rights, is a dangerous precedent. It undermines the very foundation of equality and justice that a secular state is built upon. When religious beliefs are allowed to override laws designed to protect all citizens, it creates a hierarchy of rights and privileges, leading to discrimination and inequality. The state must enforce laws uniformly to ensure that everyone, regardless of their faith, is treated equally and fairly. This approach is essential for maintaining social cohesion and protecting the rights of the most vulnerable.",
